    "description": "Awa Paper & Technological Company, Inc. manufactures and sells functional papers and non-woven fabrics in Japan, Thailand, China, rest of Asia, the United States, and internationally. The company offers automotive filter papers, clutch plate friction papers, membrane support fabrics, and battery separator papers; m-fine submerged membrane for membrane bio-reactor products, which include modules, units, wastewater treatment system packages, and microbial solutions, as well as after-sales services consisting of remote monitoring and maintenance; thermal management materials comprising M-thermo high thermal conductive, M-thermo heat conductive, and M-thermo thermal insulation materials; carbon composite materials consisting of carbon and activated carbon fiber sheets, activated carbon sheets, carbon fiber reinforced plastics, and graphite sheets; synthetic fiber papers, including polyester and polyolefin sheets; and air, oil, fuel, and nano coat filter media, as well as filter media for brewery, dry cleaning, and electronic discharge machining. It also provides inorganic powder paper comprising base papers for gaskets and meerschaum sheets; air conditioning management materials consisting of base papers for humidifiers and dehumidifiers; high performance fiber paper, including aramid sheets; and low-density thick paper products, such as cushion and impregnated papers. In addition, the company offers engine filter media; food grade paper; and functional paper for electrical and electronic components products. Its products are used in various applications, such as liquid processing, gas processing, engines, automobiles, industrial, information and communication, building materials, air conditioning, home electronics, agricultural use, and general consumer goods. Awa Paper & Technological Company, Inc. was founded in 1916 and is headquartered in Tokushima, Japan."
